 Syntax:  .listen <message_type>   or   .listen all

Results:  This command will turn off ignoring specified messages. Where 
          <message_type> is the message being ignored.  If specified with no 
          keyword, it will show what you are listening to.  The keyword all 
          will turn on all things.
              
   Note:  To ignore all messages again, type --> .ignore all

Example:  To listen to shout messages, type --> .ignore shouts

  Types:  all afks says logs shouts knocks messages topics kills
          bcasts moves echos greets picture fights atmos wiztells
          succs fails nerfs roomdescs beeps tictactoes tells colornames

See also: ignore
